snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who recently got into the SCP universe, donated to the legal fund, AND is aspiring to get an SCP published on the site one day, this video was very important to me. I thought SCP was just a gimmicky horror game just a few years ago, but now I've seen it is something much bigger and worth protecting.

Thank you for bringing more attention to this MatPat, it means a lot to know we can still win legally. (I mean without having to mail the russian a 096 mugshot)

snippet.textDisplay: I knew about this crisis months before mark or Matt made a video on this, and I thought it would have just been a sort of “closed-in” problem the SCP community would handle itself, if that makes sense. I’ve kinda always been on and off when it comes to the foundation, but I was always fond of it, and I have been for years, ever since a small little game called SCP: Containment Breach got popular on YouTube. However, this doesn’t mean I just thought “oh well, hope it gets resolved, k bai”, I saw how this could mean serious trouble for the foundation, especially in Russia, the main area being affected by this. My point is, I appreciate you and markiplier making vids on this issue, as you two would get to far more people than the foundation’s community could, and now that you have, I think stronger than ever that this problem will end favorably for the foundation, and its good and loyal employees, from the highest in the O5 Council and the ethics committee, to the lowest D-Class and janitor.
